FBIS4-18803 "drweu069_q_94011" FBIS-WEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 TURKEY Sees Role for Turkey in Peace Process Sees Role for Turkey in Peace Process TA1104062794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 2000 GMT 10 Apr 94 TA1104062794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network Turkish BFN [Text] Israel Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, who arrived in Ankara today on an official visit, has started to hold contacts. He first visited Motherland Party leader Mesut Yilmaz. Replying to journalists' questions during the meeting, Peres said that with its modern and secular structure, Turkey is exemplary in the Islamic world. Replying to a question, he said that Turkey can assume an effective role in the Middle East peace process. He added that Turkey can participate in the presence to be deployed in Jericho and Gaza. Asked what Israel expects from Turkey, Peres replied: Turkey is the only Muslim country that is friends with both the Arabs and Israel. Consequently, it can constitute a bridge factor. Shim'on Peres then met with Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin for 30 minutes. Cetin later gave a dinner in honor of the visiting foreign minister.
